column1: #Text=Artist 's representation of the Transiting Exopanet Survey Satellite .

#Text=On Wednesday at 6:51 p.m. local time ( 2251 UTC ) , a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket launched from Cape Canaveral Air Force Base in Florida , United States , carrying , as a payload for the US National Aeronautics and Space Administration ( NASA ) , the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite ( TESS ) .
#Text=NASA designed TESS to search for exoplanets circling stars mostly within 300 light-years of the Sun .

#Text=Officially a NASA Astrophysics Explorer mission , much of the TESS program is to be run from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ' s ( MIT ) Kavli Institute for Astrophysics and Space Research in cooperation with the Goddard Space Flight Center .
#Text=" One of the biggest questions in exoplanet exploration is : If an astronomer finds a planet in a star 's habitable zone , will it be interesting from a biologist 's point of view ?
